\f0\fs32 Write one program that solves two problems about nutrition: calculate a restaurant bill and calculate your body mass index (BMI). The steps are:\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 1) Restaurant bill - write code that calculates a restaurant bill given cost of food and tip percentage:\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 a) Ask for and get the cost of food. Use data type double.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 b) Ask for and get the tip percentage. Use data type double.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 c) Internally, declare the tax rate:\'a0const\'a0double tax_rate = 0.0825. Do not ask for tax rate.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 d) Compute the total bill: food cost * tax rate + tip.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 What should the tip be? Based on food cost? Food cost and tax? You decide; provide comments.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 e) Print out the total bill.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Test this. If you stop here, you have earned up to 10 points max.
