\f0\fs32 2) Body Mass Index (BMI) \'96 write code that computes BMI. The formula is:\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 BMI = (weight in pounds / (height in inches x height in inches) ) x 703\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 a) Ask for and get the required data. Use data type int.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 b) Calculate the BMI. For the result, use data type double.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 c) Print out the BMI.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Test this. If you stop here, you have earned up to 14 points max.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \cb3 3) Combine the two parts above into a menu. Prompt the user for whether they want to perform:\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 a) amount of bill; or b) BMI.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 a) Ask for and get the option desired. Use data type char.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 b) if option a, compute amount of restaurant bill; if option b, calculate BMI\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Test this. If you stop here, you have earned up to 18 points max.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \cb3 4) Loop the program, Add option q to quit. Loop until the user enters q to quit.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 a) Enter a loop.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 a) Ask for and get the option desired.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 b) if option a, compute amount of restaurant bill; if option b, calculate BMI; if option q, quit\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Test this. If you stop here, you have earned up to 20 points max.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \u8232 \cb3 Extra credit:\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 a) ignore the option\'92s case (uppercase or lowercase). Hint: use\'a0toupper() or\'a0tolower()\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 b) format the output of the bill as: $xx.xx. format the BMI as xx.xx. (display 2 decimal places)\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 c) display an error message if given an invalid option and continue the loop.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 d) ask for height in feet and inches instead of just inches; convert into inches.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 \cb3 Test this. If you stop here, you have earned up to 22 points max. This is the most possible points.
